---
import ProductLayout from '../components/layout/ProductLayout.astro';

const now = new Date().toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' });
---

<ProductLayout now={now} currentPath="/threat-map">
  <section class="page-panel grid">
    <div class="page-copy">
      <span class="page-eyebrow">Phase II foundation</span>
      <div>
        <div class="page-kicker">Threat Map</div>
        <h1 class="page-headline">Observed infrastructure and exposure geography, not theater.</h1>
      </div>
      <p>
        This surface is now a real route in the product structure. Its meaning remains deliberately
        narrow: Threat Map will represent observed infrastructure and exposure geography only, using
        conservative aggregation where source quality does not support precise points.
      </p>
      <p>
        Phase II implementation will add the underlying data contract first, then the restrained map
        interface on top of that contract. No live-attack globe, attribution theater, or customer
        geography is implied here.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="page-list">
      <div class="info-card">
        <span>Current focus</span>
        <strong>Map contract before map theatrics</strong>
        <p>Region-level aggregation and source-quality framing land before richer interaction.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <span>Guardrails</span>
        <strong>Precision follows evidence</strong>
        <p>When coordinates are unavailable, the product will fall back to coarse regional summaries.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <span>Audience fit</span>
        <strong>Leadership scan and analyst follow-up</strong>
        <p>The page is being shaped for quick regional posture review plus deeper threat inspection.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProductLayout>
